\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Client Profile
\b0 \
	The Firefighting industry has long struggled with firehose management throughout its entire existence.  The hoses are extremely large and very heavy which additionally adds significant forces within the hose, as well as forces made by the hose.  Many issues faced in hose management is personnel usage\'97meaning that there is a significant requirement of man power to simply move the hose around a fire location.  Examples can range from moving the hose up a flight to stairs, around 180 degree corners, and even over ledges and into second story windows.  With such a heavy hose there are many problems that may surface such as large magnitudes of friction as well as bend resistance.  An alternative strategy of hose management that we have devised may potentially solve a significant amount of the problems faced by fire fighters. \
	To pursue fixing the problem, we contacted Micah Holmes who works for the Longmont Fire Department.  He has been a Firefighter and Paramedic for the Longmont Fire Department for 6 years.  The Longmont Fire Department has several different stations and is responsible for the greater Longmont area.  The goal of contacting Micah is to work side by side with firefighters in developing the best possible mechanism that will diffuse the large amounts of forces presented by firehoses while operating in specific carrying parameters. 
