Design Alternatives\

\b0 	Our initial project idea began as an circular hoop with exposed ball bearings in the interior attached to a 90 degree clamp that could attach itself to a corner. After exploring the market and realizing the non-existence of these sort of parts, we went through several phases of ideas. After realizing that the individual balls that make up a ball bearing are never exposed, we decided to entertain the idea of a different system. Our first idea was to create a tubing that was bent in a 90 degree corner that would clamp over the hose and force it into a bend. This would look similar to a PVC pipe fitting and would be placed around the base of the corner, using the actual corner to brace itself from moving, as the corner would act normal to the force of the hose, as shown:\
